article.headline: N. Iowa 60, Creighton 52
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- Ali Farokhmanesh scored 15 points and Kwadzo Ahelegbe added 12 as Northern Iowa downed Creighton 60-52 Tuesday night in the Missouri Valley Conference opener for both teams. The victory was the ninth in a row for the Panthers (10-1). The preseason favorites in the MVC held the Bluejays (5-7) without a field goal for a nine-minute stretch in the first half while building a 12-point lead. UNI later answered a second-half surge by Creighton with a 14-4 run to move in front for good. The Panthers threatened to run away early as Creighton missed 15 of its first 16 shots. Cavel Witter, who finished with 17 points, hit three second-half 3-pointers as the Jays rallied to claim a 41-37 lead. Ahelegbe answered with a driving basket and a pair of free throws to spark the Panthers, who hit 16 of their 18 free-throw attempts after the break.
